PEOPLE ex rel. DARE v. GARDNER. (Supreme Court, Appellate Division, Second Department. September 29, 1916.) Appeal from Special Term, Suffolk County. Mandamus by the People, on the relation of Clarence E. Dare, against I. Willetts Gardner. From an order granting the writ, defendant appeals. Affirmed. See, also, 160 N. Y. Supp. 959.

Argued before JENKS, P. J., and THOMAS, CARR, RICH, STAPLETON, PUTNAM, and MILLS, JJ.

PER CURIAM.

Order affirmed, with $10 costs and disbursements, on authority of People ex rel. Dare v. Howell, 160 N. Y. Supp. 959, decided herewith.
